===Influence===
''[[Time Bandit]]'' (1983), best known for its 1985 [[Atari ST]] version, was heavily inspired by ''Tutankham'' and had a working title of ''Pharaoh''. Both games also have similarities to the 1985 arcade hit ''[[Gauntlet (1985 video game)|Gauntlet]]'' by [[Atari Games]]. According to ''Time Bandit'' designer Harry Lafnear, both ''Time Bandit'' and ''Gauntlet'' have roots in earlier "maze shoot 'em up" games such as ''Tutankham''.<ref name="legend">{{cite web |title=Harry Lafnear Interview |url=https://www.atarilegend.com/interviews/interviews_detail.php?selected_interview_id=4 |website=Atari Legend |date=September 5, 2003}}</ref> Jack Palevich, designer of ''Gauntlet''{{'}}s main inspiration, ''[[Dandy (video game)|Dandy]]'' (1983), also mentioned being influenced by "half-forgotten" maze-exploration arcade games which contributed the idea of using keys to unlock doors.<ref name="Palevich">{{cite web |last=Palevich |first=Jack |url=https://jacks-hacks.appspot.com/dandy/history.html |title=A History of Dandy Dungeon |accessdate=2013-11-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104190048/http://jacks-hacks.appspot.com/dandy/history.html |archivedate=2013-11-04}}</ref> In 2008, ''[[Retro Gamer]]'' magazine called ''Tutankham'' "an early ''Gauntlet''".<ref>{{cite magazine|date=August 2008|title=Developer Lookback: Konami Part I|url=https://archive.org/stream/retro_gamer/RetroGamer_053#page/n27/mode/2up|magazine=[[Retro Gamer]]|publisher=[[Imagine Publishing]]|issue=53|page=29}}</ref>

